		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Then why not just run the emulator in 3840x2160 and tell the emulator to enlarge the video by a factor of 9?<br /><br />Or are you trying to say that your video card is incapable of outputting 3840x2160 at 60 fps? I know 3840x2160 resolution on HDMI 1.x tops at out 30 fps. Is the issue that your video card doesn't support HDMI 2? Does the mouse cursor lag when you run 3840x2160 on your desktop?<br /><br />&quot;Besides, sending a signal in a display’s native resolution should always produce better image results than upscaling.&quot;<br /><br />But you're asking to add a feature to send a signal at a resolution <em>other</em> than the display's native resolution.

		

		</td>
