		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Can you not connect the TV as a secondary monitor &amp; set its resolution independently of your monitor's resolution?<br />I have a 2k computer monitor and a 1080p projector hooked to my computer, and both devices operate at different resolutions without any upscaling being applied.<br /><br />Thanks for the crash report, I can't seem to reproduce it on my end though.  <br />Does it really only happen when you exit Mesen while in fullscreen mode on your end? I can't really see why fullscreen mode would cause this kind of crash.<br />There are a few debug switches you can use on Mesen (/novideo, /noaudio, /noinput) that disable each corresponding feature, could you try if running with all or some of these prevent the crash when exiting?  This would help me get a general idea of where the bug might be.<br /><br />As far starting in fullscreen mode, this is already supported :)<br />Just use the /fullscreen command line option and Mesen will start in fullscreen mode.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
